        {
          "question": "What happens if the energy audit shows the house needs more work than weatherization covers?",
          "answer": "The program only provides weatherization services and incidental repairs needed to protect the weatherization materials. Major structural repairs or renovations are not covered. The audit determines what work is feasible within program guidelines."
        },
        {
          "question": "Can my loved one apply for this and LIEAP energy assistance at the same time?",
          "answer": "Yes, and it's actually helpful. LIEAP recipients are automatically income-eligible for weatherization, which can speed up processing. Include the LIEAP Customer ID on the weatherization application if your loved one receives energy assistance."
        },
        {
          "question": "What if we live right on the county border — which agency do we contact?",
          "answer": "Contact the agency serving the county where your loved one's home is located, not where they receive mail or have other services. Check the county map at dss.sd.gov to confirm which Community Action Agency serves that specific county."
        },
        {
          "question": "Do we have to pay anything upfront or get reimbursed later?",
          "answer": "No upfront costs for eligible homeowners. The services are completely free. Renters' landlords typically pay 1/3 of costs, but the tenant pays nothing. All work is completed before any payment is required from landlords."
        }
