      "intro": "If your loved one needs nursing home-level care but wants to stay home, South Dakota's HOPE Waiver can cover respite care, adult day services, in-home assistance, and caregiver support. Because this Medicaid waiver covers comprehensive home and community services, your loved one avoids nursing facility placement while you get the help you need as their caregiver.\n\nYour loved one qualifies if they're 65+ (or 18+ with qualifying disability), have income up to $2,901/month, assets under $2,000, and need nursing facility-level care as determined by clinical assessment. The program is capped at 1,834 recipients statewide, creating waitlists when full.\n\nServices include respite care (temporary relief for family caregivers), adult day programs, meal delivery, transportation, safety modifications, and assisted living facility placement if needed. One case management team coordinates all services, eliminating the need to manage multiple providers yourself.",
