      "intro": "If your loved one is 55+, unemployed, and has very low income (under $19,563/year for a single person in 2023), SCSEP provides part-time community service work averaging 20 hours per week at minimum wage. Because the program includes job training and placement assistance, your loved one gains work experience while earning income and building skills for permanent employment.\n\nSCSEP is only available in three regions of South Dakota: West River, East River, and Central areas (check the coverage map on the DLR website first). Veterans, those 65+, disabled individuals, and rural residents get priority enrollment. The program provides free annual physical exams and supports independence through structured work and social activities.",
