        {
          "question": "What type of community service work would my loved one do?",
          "answer": "Common placements include work at nonprofit organizations, schools, government agencies, or community service organizations. The specific assignment depends on your loved one's skills, interests, and what's available in your area."
        },
        {
          "question": "Does my loved one's house or savings count toward the income limit?",
          "answer": "No asset limits are mentioned in South Dakota's SCSEP guidelines — only the annual family income limit of 125% of Federal Poverty Level matters for eligibility."
        }
