      "intro": "If your loved one lives in a South Dakota nursing home, assisted living facility, or community living home and faces problems with care, billing, or treatment, the Long-Term Care Ombudsman provides free advocacy to resolve conflicts. The ombudsman investigates complaints, educates families about residents' rights, and mediates disputes to ensure your loved one receives fair treatment.\n\nThis service is available to any family member or resident in long-term care facilities statewide. Because ombudsmen are trained advocates who understand facility regulations, they can often resolve issues faster than families working alone. No income limits apply — the service is completely free regardless of your loved one's financial situation.",
